This Korean localization includes:
Cultural Adaptations:
Naruto terminology: 쓰기안 (Sharingan), 만화경 (Mangekyo), 영원한 만화경 쓰기안 (Eternal Mangekyo Sharingan)
Webtoon/Manhwa terms: 말풍선 (speech bubbles), 컷 (panels), 의성어·의태어 (SFX)
Korean honorifics: Native Korean explanations with proper context (~님, ~군, 선배님, etc.)
Technical Considerations:
Writing direction: References to 가로쓰기 (horizontal) and 세로쓰기 (vertical) text
Typography: Korean font considerations for Hangul and Hanja characters
Reading flow: UI elements positioned for Korean reading habits
Linguistic Features:
Polite speech level: ~습니다/~니다 form used throughout for professional tone
Onomatopoeia: Korean equivalents for Japanese SFX (두근두근, 쿵, 쩍, etc.)
Loanwords: Appropriate use of Konglish terms where standard in tech (오버레이, 모드, 캐시)
Webtoon-Specific Elements:
Platform recognition: Naver Webtoon, Daum Webtoon terminology
Vertical scrolling: References to webtoon infinite scroll format
Color terminology: Webtoon full-color vs manga monochrome distinctions
UX Localization:
Natural phrasing: "클릭하여 활성화" rather than literal translation
Status messages: Concise, clear status updates
Error handling: Polite but informative error messages (~세요, ~됩니다)
The file maintains structural parity with en.json and ja.json while providing culturally authentic Korean webtoon community terminology and proper honorific handling for Japanese content consumption.